io.github.retrooper.packetevents.processor

Class PacketProcessorInternal

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.retrooper.packetevents.processor.PacketProcessorInternal

  • public class PacketProcessorInternal
extends java.lang.Object
    Internal packet processor. This class mainly manages channel caching and internal processing. Do NOT use this class, it is only meant to be used internally.
    Since:
    1.7.9
    See Also:
    http://netty.io

      • postRead

        public void postRead(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                     java.lang.Object channel,
                     java.lang.Object packet)
        Make PacketEvents process an incoming PLAY packet after minecraft has processed it. As minecraft has already processed the packet, we cannot cancel the action, nor the event.
        Parameters:
        player - Packet sender.
        channel - Netty channel of the packet sender.
        packet - NMS Packet.

      • postWrite

        public void postWrite(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                      java.lang.Object channel,
                      java.lang.Object packet)
        Make PacketEvents process an outgoing PLAY packet after minecraft has already sent the packet. This doesn't necessarily mean the client already received the packet, but the server has sent it for sure by this time. As minecraft has already processed the packet, we cannot cancel the action, nor the event.
        Parameters:
        player - Packet receiver.
        channel - Netty channel of the packet receiver.
        packet - NMS Packet.
